<methodStep>
<description>
<section>
<title>Experimental Design</title>
<para>We sampled Betula nana root systems at intensive and extensive sites within or adjacent to the Anaktuvuk River fire burn scar two growing seasons after the fire. Sites were chosen to represent a continuous fire-severity gradient, based on the composite burn index (CBI), a fire-severity metric, between two endpoints from unburned to severely burned. Environmental data for each site were obtained from Jandt et al. (2012) and are available at www.frames.gov and with the Arctic Long-Term Ecological Research (LTER) data archive http://ecosystems.mbl.edu/arc/datacatalog.html.</para>
</section>
